HEADWORD: Dingle
<hw>Din"gle</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Of uncertain origin:
cf. AS. <ets>ding</ets> prison; or perh. akin to
<ets>dimble</ets>.]</ety> <def>A narrow dale; a small dell; a small,
secluded, and embowered valley.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

